10<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside until ready to serve."]},{"title":"Strawberry spheres","content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid (ensure bowl fits comfortably into Varoma dish) and weigh frozen strawberries into a it. Place 1000 g of the water into mixing bowl and place bowl of strawberries into Varoma. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <nobr>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Carefully remove bowl with strawberries. Transfer strawberries and any liquid into a nut milk bag or muslin cloth and strain into a separate bowl (see Tips). This strawberry 'essence' will be used to make spheres. Place essence into refrigerator to cool for approx. 30 minutes (see Tips). Discard water and dry mixing bowl.","Once cooled, place strawberry essence into mixing bowl. Add vinegar, lemon juice, salt and calcium lactate gluconate and blend <nobr>20 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add xanthan gum and mix <nobr>6 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture into a shallow container and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 30 minutes to allow large air bubbles to disperse (this may take longer than 30 minutes; small bubbles will remain). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place remaining 1000 g water into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 min\/speed 3<\/nobr> <strong>,<\/strong> <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, adding sodium alginate through hole in mixing bowl lid. Sodium alginate will dissolve and thicken to a clear, thin jelly.","If specks are still visible, scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture (spherification bath) into a container and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 1 hour to allow air bubbles to disperse. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place strawberry mixture, spherification bath, a bowl of cold water, 2 small spoons, a slotted spoon and paper towels onto kitchen bench.","Dip spoon into strawberry mixture, then wipe base of the spoon clean with paper towel. Rest spoon on surface of spherification bath then smoothly flip it over, sliding strawberry mixture into bath. Using the other spoon, gently stir bath without touching the strawberry sphere, ensuring spheres are submerged but do not rest on the base of the bath until set. Leave for 2 minutes. Carefully remove sphere with a slotted spoon and gently place into bowl of cold water.","Repeat with remaining strawberry mixture, adjusting timing as necessary to ensure spheres do not break when transferred.","Store spheres in water until ready to serve (try to allow plenty of room between them so they don't stick together). Serve within 30 minutes."]},{"title":"White chocolate powder","content":["Place white chocolate, milk and milk powder into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then cook <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until mixture is golden and caramelised. Transfer into a bowl and set aside to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Break white chocolate mixture into pieces, then place into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Scrape down base and sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add maltodextrin, then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>, until a coarse powder has formed."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Place small mounds of white chocolate powder onto 8 dessert plates. Arrange 2 mango truffles onto white chocolate powder. Place a small mound of sour meringue onto each plate. Using a slotted spoon, carefully remove a strawberry sphere from water and gently place onto meringue. Garnish with basil leaves and fresh strawberries to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Mango truffles","content":["250 g mango flesh","25 g glucose syrup","80 g white sugar","1 ½ tsp agar a